# SRE Production Safety Rules

## 1. Safety & Simulation
- **WhatIf Support**: All functions that modify state (POST, PUT, DELETE) MUST support `[CmdletBinding(SupportsShouldProcess)]`.
  - Wrap the modification logic in `if ($PSCmdlet.ShouldProcess($Target, "Operation")) { ... }`.
- **Validation**: Validate pre-conditions (e.g., Cluster health, connectivity) before attempting changes.

## 2. Observability & Logging
- **Structured Logging**: Do NOT print raw text. Log structured events including:
  - Timestamp (ISO 8601)
  - Severity (INFO, WARN, ERROR)
  - Correlation ID (Request ID)
  - Target Entity (UUID/Name)
- **Secret Sanitization**: NEVER log raw credential objects, bearer tokens, or session cookies. Use `[System.Management.Automation.PSCredential]` objects to keep secrets secure in memory.

## 3. Resilience
- **Retries**: Implement exponential backoff for transient errors (HTTP 429, 503).
  - Do NOT retry on 4xx errors (except 429).
- **Timeouts**: Explicitly define `-TimeoutSec` on all REST calls (default to 30s or 60s depending on operation).

## Examples

@example
# Production-Safe State Modification
function Remove-NtnxVmSafe {
    [CmdletBinding(SupportsShouldProcess)]
    param(
        [Parameter(Mandatory)]
        [string]$VmId
    )

    process {
        if ($PSCmdlet.ShouldProcess($VmId, "Delete Nutanix VM")) {
            try {
                $requestId = (New-Guid).ToString()
                Write-Log -Level INFO -Message "Attempting delete" -Target $VmId -RequestId $requestId

                # Retry logic for transient failures
                Invoke-RestMethodWithRetry -Uri "..." -Method DELETE -Header @{'NTNX-Request-Id' = $requestId}
            }
            catch {
                Write-Log -Level ERROR -Message "Delete failed" -Exception $_
                throw
            }
        }
    }
}